Topic : DFT and IDFT computation using DIT-FFT 
Target Audience: IV sem BE ECE students
LO: 1.Able to find DFT and IDFT of any given discrete signal.
2. Able to compute linear convolution between given sequences using DFT pair.
PI activity (15 minutes)
By means of the DFT and IDFT, determine the response of the FIR filter with impulse response h(n)={1,2,3} to the input sequence x(n)={1,2,2,1}?
a){1,4,11,9,8,3}
b){1,4,9,11,8,3}
c){1,4,9,11,3,8}
d) {1,4,9,3,8,11}

When they individually performed 8 students out of 40 responded correctly. When I did voting after their interactions it was amazingly improved to 31. Personally I feel that it must practiced to have an effective learning and also I found the healthy discussion among all the students.I decided to follow these active learning strategy make my students to  learn and attain the LOs. 

Answer: b
The input sequence has a length N=4 and impulse response has a length M=3. So, the response must have a length of 6(4+3-1).
We know that, Y(k)=X(k).H(k)
Thus we obtain Y(k)={36,-14.07-j17.48,j4,0.07+j0.515,0,0.07-j0.515,-j4,-14.07+j17.48}
By applying IDFT to the above sequence, we get y(n)={1,4,9,11,8,3,0,0}
Thus the output of the system is {1,4,9,11,8,3}.

